# PC Usage Timer  
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  
This Batch File script helps you find out how long your PC has been running by checking the **last boot time**.  
It uses the `systeminfo` command to retrieve system details and extracts the **System Boot Time**.  
This is useful to monitor uptime or check how long the system has been in use.  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# STEPS  
1. Open Notepad  
2. Copy and Paste the Following Code  
3. Save the File as a Batch File (`uptime.bat`)  
4. Run `uptime.bat`  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# CODE  
@echo off  
title PC Usage Timer  
cls  

echo ===================================  
echo         PC USAGE TIMER  
echo ===================================  
echo Fetching system boot time...  
echo.  

systeminfo | find "System Boot Time"  

echo.  
echo ===================================  
pause  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------  

# Usage Tips  
1. Run `uptime.bat`.  
2. It will display the **System Boot Time** (the last time your PC was turned on or restarted).  
3. Use this info to calculate how long the PC has been running.  
4. You can run this script anytime to monitor your PC uptime.  
5. Press any key to exit.  

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
